rComments: MAT224 is so good with this guy! Interesting, lots of examples. He really, I mean REALLY, likes polynomials, lol. An interesting course, and nice lectures/office hours. The textbook was subpar, but I did not need it except for exercises (he posts his own exercises anyway, though more difficult ...) Would take him again :D
A very nice course saved my GPA! He can explain theory in examples, and he explains examples better than TAs. It was a pity see him walking with a crutch for a while... Nice prof I had!
This guy is an absolute must, if you want to learn how to do math! Sometimes theory is not quite clear, but then you realize everything through many examples. Always gives nice explanation.
Really a teacher. Sometimes slow in the lectures, though overall clear, approachable and nice!

Gives very detailed lectures, with lots of examples, rather than theory. He tends to repeat things over sometimes (may be feels some ppl don't quite follow, that's why). In principal, explains everything twice, some theory + some practice, gives lots of term tests (4 term tests!), which are short. He makes review sections though! Overall, good.
